-- pg_turbovec v1.3.0 -- Phase Q: side-table storage retired.
--
-- This file is a *reference mirror*. The authoritative install
-- script is generated by `cargo pgrx schema`.
--
-- v1.3.0 removes the SPI side-table `turbovec.am_storage` that the
-- AM used in v1.0.x..v1.1.0 and the v1 (Phase L preview) relfile
-- meta layout used in v1.2.0. The relfile-resident page format
-- with the persisted SIMD-blocked layout + Lloyd-Max codebook
-- (Phase P, v2 wire format) is now the only storage strategy.
--
-- ## Migration
--
-- Any existing turbovec index built under v1.0.x..v1.2.0 must be
-- rebuilt before it is queryable on v1.3.0:
--
--   ALTER EXTENSION pg_turbovec UPDATE TO '1.3.0';
--   REINDEX INDEX <every_turbovec_index>;
--
-- Without REINDEX, `ambeginscan` raises an `ERROR` (no longer a
-- `NOTICE`) explaining the situation. This is a deliberate hard
-- migration boundary -- a half-broken state can't silently
-- return zero rows.
--
-- ## What the install script does
--
-- - Drops `turbovec.am_storage` if it still exists (legacy state
--   from a previous install).
-- - Registers `turbovec_index_handler` and the `turbovec` access
--   method (unchanged from v1.2.0).
-- - Creates the `vec_ip_ops`, `vec_cosine_ops`, `vec_l2_ops`,
--   `vec_l1_ops` operator classes (unchanged from v1.2.0).
--
-- The Cargo feature flags `experimental_index_am` and
-- `relfile_storage` are also retired in v1.3.0; the only build
-- knob that remains is `pg<N>` to select the PostgreSQL major
-- version.

SET search_path = turbovec, public;

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS turbovec.am_storage CASCADE;
